item.title: Latent Feature Relation Consistency for Adversarial Robustness
item.description: Deep neural networks have been applied in many computer vision tasks and achieved state-of-the-art performance.

item.title: End-to-End $n$-ary Relation Extraction for Combination Drug Therapies
item.description: Extracting combination therapies from scientific literature inherently constitutes an $n$-ary relation extraction problem.

item.description: Image generation using diffusion can be controlled in multiple ways.

item.title: Neuro-symbolic Rule Learning in Real-world Classification Tasks
item.description: Neuro-symbolic rule learning has attracted lots of attention as it offers better interpretability than pure neural models and scales better than symbolic rule learning.

item.title: TriVol: Point Cloud Rendering via Triple Volumes
item.description: However, artifacts still appear in rendered images, due to the challenges in extracting continuous and discriminative 3D features from point clouds.

item.title: Robust Dancer: Long-term 3D Dance Synthesis Using Unpaired Data
item.description: How to automatically synthesize natural-looking dance movements based on a piece of music is an incrementally popular yet challenging task.

item.title: Local Interpretability of Random Forests for Multi-Target Regression
item.description: Although model-agnostic techniques exist for multi-target regression, specific techniques tailored to random forest models are not available.

item.title: DPF: Learning Dense Prediction Fields with Weak Supervision
item.description: We showcase the effectiveness of DPFs using two substantially different tasks: high-level semantic parsing and low-level intrinsic image decomposition.

item.title: From axioms over graphs to vectors, and back again: evaluating the properties of graph-based ontology embeddings
item.description: Several approaches have been developed that generate embeddings for Description Logic ontologies and use these embeddings in machine learning.

item.title: DORT: Modeling Dynamic Objects in Recurrent for Multi-Camera 3D Object Detection and Tracking
item.description: Recent multi-camera 3D object detectors usually leverage temporal information to construct multi-view stereo that alleviates the ill-posed depth estimation.

item.title: AraSpot: Arabic Spoken Command Spotting
item.description: Spoken keyword spotting (KWS) is the task of identifying a keyword in an audio stream and is widely used in smart devices at the edge in order to activate voice assistants and perform hands-free tasks.

item.title: HybridPoint: Point Cloud Registration Based on Hybrid Point Sampling and Matching
item.description: Firstly, we propose to use salient points with prominent local features as nodes to increase patch repeatability, and introduce some uniformly distributed points to complete the point cloud, thus constituting hybrid points.

item.title: Generalized Relation Modeling for Transformer Tracking
item.description: Compared with previous two-stream trackers, the recent one-stream tracking pipeline, which allows earlier interaction between the template and search region, has achieved a remarkable performance gain.

item.title: An intelligent modular real-time vision-based system for environment perception
item.description: Each section is accompanied by novel techniques to improve the accuracy of others along with the entire system.

item.title: Photometric LiDAR and RGB-D Bundle Adjustment
item.description: This paper presents a novel BA photometric strategy that accounts for both RGB-D and LiDAR in the same way.

item.title: 4D Facial Expression Diffusion Model
item.description: It is composed of two tasks: (1) Learning the generative model that is trained over a set of 3D landmark sequences, and (2) Generating 3D mesh sequences of an input facial mesh driven by the generated landmark sequences.

item.title: AutoAD: Movie Description in Context
item.description: The objective of this paper is an automatic Audio Description (AD) model that ingests movies and outputs AD in text form.

item.title: Implicit Diffusion Models for Continuous Super-Resolution
item.description: IDM integrates an implicit neural representation and a denoising diffusion model in a unified end-to-end framework, where the implicit neural representation is adopted in the decoding process to learn continuous-resolution representation.

item.title: Multi-View Azimuth Stereo via Tangent Space Consistency
item.description: We present a method for 3D reconstruction only using calibrated multi-view surface azimuth maps.

item.title: InceptionNeXt: When Inception Meets ConvNeXt
item.description: Inspired by the long-range modeling ability of ViTs, large-kernel convolutions are widely studied and adopted recently to enlarge the receptive field and improve model performance, like the remarkable work ConvNeXt which employs 7x7 depthwise convolution.

item.title: Multi-scale Hierarchical Vision Transformer with Cascaded Attention Decoding for Medical Image Segmentation
item.description: Transformers have shown great success in medical image segmentation.

item.title: Importance Sampling for Stochastic Gradient Descent in Deep Neural Networks
item.description: Stochastic gradient descent samples uniformly the training set to build an unbiased gradient estimate with a limited number of samples.

item.description: Tested on our second, independent, and public NNS in-the-wild dataset, NNS recognition classification reaches 92. 3\% accuracy, and NNS segmentation achieves 90. 8\% precision and 84. 2\% recall.

item.title: Your Diffusion Model is Secretly a Zero-Shot Classifier
item.description: Finally, we use Diffusion Classifier to extract standard classifiers from class-conditional diffusion models trained on ImageNet.

item.title: HOICLIP: Efficient Knowledge Transfer for HOI Detection with Vision-Language Models
item.description: In detail, we first introduce a novel interaction decoder to extract informative regions in the visual feature map of CLIP via a cross-attention mechanism, which is then fused with the detection backbone by a knowledge integration block for more accurate human-object pair detection.

item.title: PhaBOX: A web server for identifying and characterizing phage contigs in metagenomic data
item.description: To our best knowledge, this is the first web server that supports integrated phage analysis, including detecting phage contigs from the metagenomic assembly, lifestyle prediction, taxonomic classification, and host prediction.

item.title: Forecasting localized weather impacts on vegetation as seen from space with meteo-guided video prediction
item.description: We present a novel approach for modeling vegetation response to weather in Europe as measured by the Sentinel 2 satellite.

item.title: Uncovering the Missing Pattern: Unified Framework Towards Trajectory Imputation and Prediction
item.description: As far as we know, this is the first work to address the lack of benchmarks and techniques for trajectory imputation and prediction in a unified manner.

item.title: Thread Counting in Plain Weave for Old Paintings Using Semi-Supervised Regression Deep Learning Models
item.description: In this work the authors develop regression approaches based on deep learning to perform thread density estimation for plain weave canvas analysis.

item.title: Metrics for Dataset Demographic Bias: A Case Study on Facial Expression Recognition
item.description: One of the most prominent types of demographic bias are statistical imbalances in the representation of demographic groups in the datasets.

item.title: X-Mesh: Towards Fast and Accurate Text-driven 3D Stylization via Dynamic Textual Guidance
item.description: Text-driven 3D stylization is a complex and crucial task in the fields of computer vision (CV) and computer graphics (CG), aimed at transforming a bare mesh to fit a target text.

item.description: Therefore, their performance is unreliable for JIT decision making.

item.description: A consistency loss is then enforced on the found matches.

item.title: qEUBO: A Decision-Theoretic Acquisition Function for Preferential Bayesian Optimization
item.description: Preferential Bayesian optimization (PBO) is a framework for optimizing a decision maker's latent utility function using preference feedback.

item.title: Novel View Synthesis of Humans using Differentiable Rendering
item.description: We show how our approach can be used for motion transfer between individuals; novel view synthesis of individuals captured from just a single camera; to synthesize individuals from any virtual viewpoint; and to re-render people in novel poses.

item.title: 4K-HAZE: A Dehazing Benchmark with 4K Resolution Hazy and Haze-Free Images
item.description: The challenges in building ultra-high-definition (UHD) dehazing datasets are the absence of estimation methods for UHD depth maps, high-quality 4K depth estimation datasets, and migration strategies for UHD haze images from synthetic to real domains.

item.title: Multi-Behavior Recommendation with Cascading Graph Convolution Networks
item.description: Most existing multi-behavior models fail to capture such dependencies in a behavior chain for embedding learning.

item.title: Offline RL with No OOD Actions: In-Sample Learning via Implicit Value Regularization
item.description: This gives a deeper understanding of why the in-sample learning paradigm works, i. e., it applies implicit value regularization to the policy.

item.title: One Adapter for All Programming Languages? Adapter Tuning for Code Search and Summarization
item.description: To alleviate the potentially catastrophic forgetting issue in multilingual models, we fix all pre-trained model parameters, insert the parameter-efficient structure adapter, and fine-tune it.

item.title: KERM: Knowledge Enhanced Reasoning for Vision-and-Language Navigation
item.description: The proposed KERM can automatically select and gather crucial and relevant cues, obtaining more accurate action prediction.

item.title: Unmasked Teacher: Towards Training-Efficient Video Foundation Models
item.description: Previous VFMs rely on Image Foundation Models (IFMs), which face challenges in transferring to the video domain.

item.title: PosterLayout: A New Benchmark and Approach for Content-aware Visual-Textual Presentation Layout
item.description: Content-aware visual-textual presentation layout aims at arranging spatial space on the given canvas for pre-defined elements, including text, logo, and underlay, which is a key to automatic template-free creative graphic design.

item.title: SVD-DIP: Overcoming the Overfitting Problem in DIP-based CT Reconstruction
item.description: The deep image prior (DIP) is a well-established unsupervised deep learning method for image reconstruction; yet it is far from being flawless.

item.title: On Feature Scaling of Recursive Feature Machines
item.description: In this technical report, we explore the behavior of Recursive Feature Machines (RFMs), a type of novel kernel machine that recursively learns features via the average gradient outer product, through a series of experiments on regression datasets.

item.title: Scalable, Detailed and Mask-Free Universal Photometric Stereo
item.description: In this paper, we introduce SDM-UniPS, a groundbreaking Scalable, Detailed, Mask-free, and Universal Photometric Stereo network.

item.title: Efficient Quality Diversity Optimization of 3D Buildings through 2D Pre-optimization
item.description: For a use case to design buildings that minimize wind nuisance, we show that we can predict flow features around 3D buildings from 2D flow features around building footprints.

item.title: Projected Latent Distillation for Data-Agnostic Consolidation in Distributed Continual Learning
item.description: We formalize this problem as a Distributed Continual Learning scenario, where SCD adapt to local tasks and a CL model consolidates the knowledge from the resulting stream of models without looking at the SCD's private data.

item.title: Unsupervised Pre-Training For Data-Efficient Text-to-Speech On Low Resource Languages
item.description: We empirically demonstrate the effectiveness of our proposed method in low-resource language scenarios, achieving outstanding performance compared to competing methods.

item.title: Genetic Analysis of Prostate Cancer with Computer Science Methods
item.description: Metastatic prostate cancer is one of the most common cancers in men.

item.title: Comparison of HDR quality metrics in Per-Clip Lagrangian multiplier optimisation with AV1
item.description: The complexity of modern codecs along with the increased need of delivering high-quality videos at low bitrates has reinforced the idea of a per-clip tailoring of parameters for optimised rate-distortion performance.
